WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.703
Expanded Functions of Dental Assistants

00:00:02.703 --> 00:00:07.392
Dental assistants may have varying responsibilities depending on state regulations.

00:00:07.392 --> 00:00:10.099
Common expanded functions include:

00:00:10.099 --> 00:00:16.500
Placing Sealants:** 
Applying sealants to the chewing surfaces of teeth to prevent cavities, particularly in children.

00:00:16.500 --> 00:00:22.903
Taking Impressions:** 
Accurately capturing dental impressions, essential for creating crowns and other appliances.

00:00:22.903 --> 00:00:29.945
Fabricating Temporary Crowns:** 
Making temporary crowns to protect prepared teeth while waiting for permanent restorations.

00:00:29.945 --> 00:00:37.287
Applying Fluoride Treatments:** 
Administering fluoride varnishes or gels to strengthen enamel and prevent decay in at-risk patients.

00:00:37.287 --> 00:00:43.345
These functions help streamline dental practices and improve patient care under the supervision of licensed dentists.
